Adjust rack to top position and preheat oven to 425 degrees. Wash and dry all produce.

Dice @Yukon Gold Potatoes{12%ounce} into ½-inch pieces (no need to peel). Trim and
thinly slice @scallions{2%unit}(trimmed and thinly sliced), separating whites
from greens. Trim and halve @Brussels Sprouts{8%ounce}(trimmed and halved) lengthwise.

Place potatoes in a #medium pot{} with enough salted water to cover by 2 inches.
Bring to a boil and cook until tender, ~{15-20%minutes}. Reserve ½ cup potato
cooking liquid, then drain and return potatoes to pot.

Mash potatoes with half the @sour cream{4%tablespoon} (you'll use the rest later)
and @butter{1%tablespoon}, adding splashes of reserved potato cooking liquid as
needed until smooth and creamy.

Stir in half the scallion greens. Season with @salt{} and @pinch of pepper{}. Keep
covered until ready to serve.

> 4 SERVINGS: Use 2 TBSP butter.

== Roasted Brussels Sprouts ==

While potatoes cook, toss Brussels sprouts on a #baking sheet{} with a drizzle
of @vegetable oil{1%tablespoon} and a big pinch of salt and pepper. Roast on top
rack until browned and tender, ~{18-22%minutes}.

== Brown Sugar Bourbon Steak ==

Meanwhile, pat @ranch steak{10%ounce} dry with #paper towels{}; season all over
with half the @McCormick Grill Mates Brown Sugar Bourbon Seasoning{10.8%g} (you'll
use the rest in the next step).

Heat a drizzle of oil in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add steak and cook
to desired doneness, ~{3-6%minutes} per side. Turn off heat; transfer to a
#cutting board{} to rest.

> TIP: Lower heat if spice blend begins to burn.

== Creamy Dijon Pan Sauce ==

Heat another drizzle of oil in #same pan{} over medium heat. Add scallion whites
and remaining McCormick Grill Mates Brown Sugar Bourbon Seasoning. Cook, stirring,
until scallion whites are softened and fragrant, ~{1%minute}.

Stir in @beef stock concentrate{1%unit} and @water{1/4%cup}. Simmer until slightly
thickened, ~{2-3%minutes}. Reduce heat to low and whisk in @Dijon mustard{2%teaspoon}.

Turn off heat; stir in remaining sour cream and @butter{1%tablespoon}.

> 4 SERVINGS: Use 1/3 cup water and 2 TBSP butter.

== To Serve ==

Slice steak against the grain. Divide potatoes, Brussels sprouts, and steak
between plates. Spoon sauce over steak. Sprinkle with remaining scallion greens
and serve.